</P>
<P>
   HOME-SECURITY _ Home security need not be an expensive or
difficult thing to achieve. Story looks at simple and inexpensive
ways to feel safe at home. (Rocky Mount Telegram). 20. WITH PHOTOS.
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Lee May's gardening column is not available
this week.
</P>
<P>
   KITCHEN-FLOOR _ Installing a kitchen floor has come a long way
from the old days of rolling out a sheet of Congoleum. Costs alone
can be major _ especially when you consider that surface materials
are just one expense in furnishing a kitchen. There are also a
variety of options these day that include: hardwoods, stone,
laminates, vinyls and ceramics. In order to help with the choices,
we had flooring experts rate each floor on looks, strength, feel,
cleanup and costs. As an added treat, we invited two chefs (who
spend long hours on their feet) to weigh in on the flooring
options. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, March 9.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DREAM-KITCHEN _ Jackie Cottrill recently spent about $150,000 on
kitchen renovations. Cottrill knew exactly what she wanted in an
upscale Atlanta home. After all, it was her 18th house in 25 years,
and she has designed or decorated every one of them. The kitchen is
highend, yet it's jammed with cost-saving ideas. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
