think of race relations as yesterday's news. Discrimination by
government or business is prohibited, right? So all we need to to
is make sure the streets are passable, the police are on call,
education and jobs are available, right? All will be well as we
reside in our neutral corners. Right? Not even close. Chaos or
community. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
