C. Katz, a professor of neurobiology at Duke University Medical
School in North Carolina, promotes a regimen called ``neurobics,''
in which he encourages people to stretch the gray matter doing such
simple things as brushing their teeth with the opposite hand or
taking a new route to work. By SYLVIA WOOD.
</P>
