of monsters, critters and funny, saucy children. While some of
these creatures are three-dimensional (such as her two daughters),
many are painted extensions of the book illustrator's deeply
inventive, childlike imagination. Rogers' latest book, ``Fairies,
Trolls and Goblins Galore,'' is her third poetry picture book on
the subject of scary beasts and the children who love them. By KRIS
WORRELL.
