<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CONROY-FIRE _ ATLANTA _A massive fire destroyed the former home
of author Pat Conroy and damaged two other houses today in one of
Atlanta's oldest neighborhoods. The fire broke out about 3 a.m. EST
in the kitchen of a two-story, wood-frame home at 34 Peachtree
Circle in Ansley Park -- one the market for $900,000 -- and quickly
spread to two adjacent houses. Conroy lived in the house in the
1980s and wrote ``Prince of Tides'' there, according to a neighbor.
(Davis-Reid, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   HISPANICS-SOUTH _ The Hispanic population in the U.S. South is
growing at a faster rate than the Hispanic population elsewhere in
the country, according to a report released Wed. March 8 by the
U.S. Census Bureau. About 1 in 3 Hispnaics live in the South. Other
findings: Hispanics have lower education and income levels than
non-Hispanic whites, but there are dramatic differences between
subgroups of Hispanics - between Cubans, Mexicans and Puetro
Ricans, for instance. That info contradicts a widely help
perception of Hispanics as a monolithic population, the government
says. (Bixler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-AFFIRM _ TALLAHASSEE _ Thousands of people were expected to
march on the Old Capitol building Tuesday to protest Gov. Jeb
Bush's new policy making university admissions and contracting
decisions race- and gender-blind. Martin Luther King III and Jesse
Jackson will be among them. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MARDIGRAS _ NEW ORLEANS _ The scene on Fat Tuesday in the Big
Easy. (Konigsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN _ WASHINGTON - Despite a recent rash incidents involving
food purchased by the federal government for the nation's school
lunch program, the U.S. General Accounting office said in a report
released Tuesday that its investigation found few problems.
(Jaspin, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   RAILROADS _ WASHINGTON _ Hearings begin Tuesday that could lead
the way to tougher scrutiny of rail mergers and criticism that
there isn't enough competition. A chief target of those worried
about merger mania is the plan by Burlington Northern Santa Fe
Corp. and Canadian National Railway Co. to create North America's
largest carrier. (Turay, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   TEACHER-TESTS _ WASHINGTON _ The long-awaited report of the
National Research Council on the quality of state teacher-licensing
exams, and whether they are any good at identifying effective
teachers is released Tuesday. (Mollison, Cox News Service)
</P>
