<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-07 15:21 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9424 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r l BC-AIR-FILTERS-HNS &LR;      03-07 0313
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AIR-FILTERS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     TECHNOLOGY CAN HELP REDUCE POLLUTANTS AT HOME 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By FRANCES INGRAHAM HEINS  
 &HT;     c.2000 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Many of us retreat to our homes for relaxation and security,
only to find that our senses are being attacked by a variety of
allergy-related culprits.
</P>
<P>
   The Environmental Protection Agency and the American Lung
Association say that indoor air pollution is a major health
concern.
</P>
<P>
   According to PuriTec, makers of air cleaners, the air in your
home may be four to 100 times more polluted than that in even large
cities like Los Angeles and Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   One way to combat airborne irritants is to use an air cleaner to
clear tobacco smoke, pet hair and dander, dust mites, molds,
bacteria and pollen. It can also remove vapors from carpets and
textiles, cleaning solvents and other pollution particulates that
exacerbate allergies and asthma.
</P>
<P>
   Clean air allows you to sleep and breathe easier.
</P>
<P>
   When choosing an air cleaner, look for a free-standing model
that combines the latest technology in high-efficiency particulate
absorption, or HEPA, and carbon air filtration, which in a larger
form is the type used in hospital surgery rooms.
</P>
<P>
   HEPA technology, which has been around since the 1930s, is
essentially a type of paper that allows air to pass through while
absorbing and trapping pollutants, preventing them from moving back
into the air.
</P>
<P>
   HEPA technology was developed by the Atomic Energy Commission to
create clean and safe environments to protect researchers and
scientists. High-efficiency gas absorption, or HEGA, filtration was
released in 1998 by the British Army for use by the public. This
type of filter, which uses a granular mix, was designed to protect
troops from chemical weapons and in air cleaners to remove
formaldehyde and acetones.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
