<HEADLINE>
HOW WELL DOES `POPULAR' LIVE UP TO ITS NAME?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What's the background of the producers and writers of the TV
show ``Popular,'' and how is it doing in the ratings? The episode I
just saw was particularly disturbing and obscene.
</P>
<P>
   _ C.R., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Popular,'' a WB network sitcom that premiered in September
1999, is credited to screenwriter Ryan Murphy and film producer
Gina Matthews. Murphy wrote ``The Furies'' and ``Why Can't I Be
Audrey Hepburn?'' and Matthews produced ``Urban Legend.''
</P>
<P>
   You can write to the crew and cast in care of ``Popular,'' WB
Network, 4000 Warner Blvd., Bldg. No. 34R, Burbank, CA 91522.
</P>
<P>
   There are two ways to look at the ratings for the show, which is
watched by about 2.5 million viewers. About 80 to 90 shows have
higher ratings each week, but the comedy is the most popular sitcom
and seventh-most-popular show on the WB network.
</P>
<P>
   Recently, WB replaced two new shows with ``Popular'' reruns on
Monday nights: ``Brutally Normal'' and ``Zoe.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: I met someone who resembles the very beautiful '50s model
Bettie Page. Where can I get a photo of her?
</P>
<P>
   _ J., Granbury, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The retailer What's Hot Now sells 20 official Bettie Page
items, including lighters, coffee mugs, money clips and T-shirts.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (888) 500-7776 or visit the Web site www.whn.com.
Page also has an official Web site at www.cmgww.com/stars/page.
</P>
<P>
   Page, 76, quit modeling in 1957 and later worked as a counselor
for the Billy Graham Crusades and as an elementary school teacher.
She lives in the Los Angeles area today and turns down frequent
public-appearance and photo requests.
</P>
<P>
   ``No one wants to see a fat old model,'' she told the
Minneapolis Star-Tribune in 1997. ``It destroys the image.''
</P>
<P>
   Fans can write to her in care of Page's official fan club, the
Bettie Scouts of America, at 2641 S. 53rd St., Kansas City, KS
66106-3365.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I mail something to Jay Leno and David Letterman?
</P>
<P>
   _ U.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Leno in care of ``The Tonight Show With Jay Leno,''
NBC Productions, 3000 W. Alameda Ave., Burbank, CA 91523, or visit
the Web site www.nbc.com/tonightshow.
</P>
<P>
   Write to Letterman in care of ``Late Show With David
Letterman,'' 1697 Broadway, 12th Floor, New York, NY 10019, or send
e-mail to lswdl(at)aol.com.
</P>
<P>
   ``Late Show'' is taking orders for Dave's Official Bypass
T-shirt, a white shirt with a surgical scar commemorating
Letterman's January quintuple bypass surgery. You can order it for
$14.95 by calling (800) 699-3579 or visiting the Web site
www.wpsuperstore.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
