r d BC-SHORTCUTS-LADN 2ndadd &LR;    03-07 0933
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHORTCUTS-LADN, </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 2nd add  
UNDATED: ... cheese for a hearty dip. MICROWAVE HALIBUT AND VEGETABLES
<TEXT>
<P>
   This is one of the fastest and most delicious ways to prepare
fish. The recipe works well with soft as well as firm fish. Figure
about 7 minutes of microwaving time per pound of fish. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 (16-ounce) package frozen zucchini, mushrooms, pearl onions and
carrots OR any other frozen vegetable combination desired &QL; 
1 pound halibut steaks, 3/4-inch thick &QL; 
1 lemon &QL; 
1 1/2 teaspoons dried dill weed &QL; 
2 medium tomatoes, chopped &QL; 
1 medium green bell pepper, chopped &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon garlic salt
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon pepper
</P>
<P>
   Place package of frozen vegetables on a double thickness of
paper plates. Pierce holes in a couple of places in top of package
with a knife. Cook in microwave oven on high power 7 to 8 minutes,
or until thawed and partially cooked. Drain off excess water; set
vegetables aside.
</P>
<P>
   Arrange fish in a 10-inch pie plate or oval microwave-safe
baking dish. Squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon over fish and sprinkle with
dill weed. Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap. Cook in
microwave on high 3 1/2 minutes, turning dish once during cooking
time. Remove from oven and drain off and discard any excess liquid
from dish.
</P>
<P>
   Place tomatoes, green pepper and partially cooked vegetables on
top and around sides of fish. Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Squeeze juice of remaining 1/2 lemon over top. Cover with plastic
wrap. Return to microwave and cook on high 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes,
or until fish flakes easily when pierced with a fork.
</P>
<P>
   Serve fish with vegetables. Garnish with lemon wedges. Makes 4
servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``365 Easy One-Dish Meals'' by Natalie Haughton (Harper &AMP;
Row).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
SOUTHWESTERN CORN SALAD &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 (15-ounce) can black-eyed peas OR black beans, drained and
rinsed &QL; 
1 (11-ounce) can Mexicorn, drained &QL; 
1/4 cup finely chopped red onion &QL; 
1/4 cup finely chopped fresh cilantro &QL; 
1/4 cup vegetable oil &QL; 
1/4 cup fresh lime juice &QL; 
1 teaspoon seeded, finely chopped serrano OR jalapeno chile OR a
few dashes Tabasco sauce
</P>
<P>
   Combine black-eyed peas, Mexicorn, red onion, cilantro, lime
juice and chile in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to
blend flavors. Serve on lettuce. Makes 6 (1/2-cup) side-dish
servings OR 3 (1-cup) entree servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
APPLE AND GREEN CHILE SALAD &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
2 cups (2 medium) chopped red and green apples &QL; 
1 cup (2 large stalks) sliced celery &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped walnuts, toasted &QL; 
1/2 to 1 (4-ounce) can diced green chiles &QL; 
1/3 cup prepared ranch-style salad dressing &QL; 
1/4 cup mayonnaise &QL; 
Lettuce leaves (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Combine apples, celery, nuts, chiles, salad dressing and
mayonnaise in a medium bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Cover, refrigerate 1 hour. Serve over lettuce leaves. Makes 6
servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SKILLET CHICKEN FAJITAS &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1/4 cup fresh lime juice &QL; 
1/4 cup picante sauce &QL; 
4 boneless, skinless chicken breast halves, cut into thin strips &QL; 
Salt and pepper &QL; 
1 large onion, thinly sliced &QL; 
1 large red OR green bell pepper, cut into thin strips &QL; 
Choice of toppings: chopped tomato, shredded cheese, dairy sour
cream, avocado slices OR guacamole and salsa &QL; 
4 to 8 flour tortillas
</P>
<P>
   Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
</P>
<P>
   Combine lime juice and picante sauce and use to coat chicken
well. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
</P>
<P>
   Stir-fry chicken over medium-high heat until cooked through,
about 7 to 8 minutes. Remove to a plate. Stir-fry onion and pepper
in same skillet until crisp-tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, prepare toppings and heat tortillas. To heat
tortillas, wrap in a damp paper towel; microwave on high power 30
seconds, or until warm.
</P>
<P>
   Serve chicken and onions and peppers on hot tortillas and wrap
up with desired toppings. Makes 3 to 4 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOUPER CHICKEN TETRAZZINI &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
8 ounces uncooked spaghetti &QL; 
Water &QL; 
2 tablespoons butter &QL; 
2 cups sliced fresh mushrooms &QL; 
1 small onion, chopped &QL; 
2 (10 3/4-ounce) cans condensed cream of chicken OR mushroom soup &QL; 
1 soup can milk &QL; 
2 tablespoons dry sherry &QL; 
2 cups cubed cooked chicken &QL; 
1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese &QL; 
1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
</P>
<P>
   Cook spaghetti in boiling water according to package directions;
drain.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, in a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot
butter, cook mushrooms and onion until tender, stirring
occasionally. Stir in soup, milk and sherry; heat through.
</P>
<P>
   Return cooked spaghetti to cooking pot. Add soup mixture,
chicken, Parmesan and parsley. Toss lightly until spaghetti is
coated. Over medium heat, heat through.
</P>
<P>
   Serve with additional Parmesan, if desired. Makes 6 cups or 4
servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CHILI DOG CASSEROLE &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
2 (15-ounce) cans chili with beans &QL; 
1 (16-ounce) package beef franks &QL; 
10 (8-inch) corn OR flour tortillas &QL; 
1 (8-ounce) package shredded mild Cheddar cheese
</P>
<P>
   Spoon 1 can chili into a 13x9-inch baking pan.
</P>
<P>
   Roll up beef franks inside tortillas. Place in a baking dish,
seam-side down. Top with remaining can chili and cheese. Cover pan
with foil.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 425-degree oven 30 minutes. Makes 10
servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CREAMY CHOCOLATE PIE &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 3/4 cups cold milk &QL; 
2 (4-serving size) packages chocolate OR chocolate fudge flavor
INSTANT pudding and pie filling mix &QL; 
1 (8-ounce) tub frozen whipped topping, thawed &QL; 
1 prepared chocolate flavor crumb crust (6 ounces)
</P>
<P>
   Pour milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with a wire
whisk just until mixed. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir
in thawed topping.
</P>
<P>
   Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish as
desired. Store leftover pie in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
END &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
