<P>
   UNDATED _ Amtrak's decision to change its route through Texas
isn't being celebrated in Alpine, Sanderson and Del Rio, the cities
along the old route that have been summarily abandoned. ``This
particular route change is shortsighted when considering the big
picture of tourism and the picturesque Sunset Limited itinerary,''
says David Busey, director of community development in Alpine. By
ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
