will result from rising interest rates, investors now have to worry
about the ill effects of higher materials costs on company earnings
this year. The Dow Jones industrial average took the biggest hit,
falling 374.47 points, or 3.68 percent. Broader market averages
fared a bit better. By Gretchen Morgenson and Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
