<P>
   REPUBLICAN-PRIMARIES (Undated) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush
effectively silences the challenge of Sen. John McCain for the
Republican presidential nomination, setting the stage for Bush to
court McCain and his supporters to join in a GOP crusade in the
November election. Bush harnessed hard-hitting campaign ads and a
lavishly financed nationwide campaign organization to roll up
victories in at least eight of the 13 states with GOP contests,
according exit polls. By STEWART M. POWELL and DAN FREEDMAN. (Will
update.)
</P>
