<P>
   BRADLEY-ANALYSIS (Undated) _ True, a few things that led to Bill
Bradley's undoing in the Democratic presidential race were beyond
his control, such as Al Gore evolving into a better campaigner and
John McCain's strength among independents. But at the core,
Bradley's demise can be called the death of a non-salesman. His
inability or reluctance to be a gut-level pitchman for his own
lofty message prevented him from overriding the outside factors. By
ALAN BERNSTEIN. (Already filed.)
</P>
