<HEADLINE>
BRUINS HAVE MUDDLE IN THE MIDDLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA's riddle begins in the middle. It's either
awesome or awful, depending on the play of sophomore big men Jerome
Moiso and Dan Gadzuric, who are either dominant or dormant.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have the talent, there's no doubt,'' Moiso said. ``But
we've also been struggling.''
</P>
<P>
   Three weeks ago, Moiso scored six points and grabbed one rebound
at Arizona State. Saturday, he dominated Stanford with 12 rebounds
and 17 points _ including eight in the final minutes of regulation.
</P>
<P>
   Three weeks ago, Gadzuric scored eight points and grabbed six
rebounds at Arizona State. Last week, he dominated Cal with a
career-high 22 points and 16 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``With both, because of the fact that they're from overseas
(Gadzuric is Dutch, Moiso's from Guadeloupe in the West Indies) . .
. we have to be more patient with them,'' Bruins coach Steve Lavin
said. ``We have to understand that they aren't going to play
consistently at the level of Lew Alcindor or Bill Walton.''
</P>
<P>
   Not even the most deluded UCLA fans have asked them to play like
Walton or Alcindor. The Bruins simply need Gadzuric and Moiso to be
impact players on a weekly basis. In the Bay Area, they were. Will
it last?
</P>
<P>
   UCLA's postseason success depends on the mystery men in the
middle.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm getting more confident,'' Gadzuric said. ``I'm learning
more about recognizing defenses so I know when the double team is
coming and can find the open man. In the game, it all happens in
the snap of your fingers.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Solid sophs: Gadzuric, Moiso, Ray Young, Matt Barnes and
JaRon Rush arrived 18 months ago as one of the nation's top rookie
classes. Each has excelled at various times, but Saturday's
performance at Stanford was their best collective effort.
</P>
<P>
   Rush scored a team-high 19 points and hit the game-winner. Moiso
dominated in the final minutes of regulation. Gadzuric had 10
points before fouling out. Barnes had 10 points and three assists
off the bench, and Young played 16 minutes without a turnover.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the first time I can remember all five playing well at
the same time,'' Lavin said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Odds and ends: The Bruins have won four in a row for the
first time this season.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA is 6-2 in overtime games under Lavin.
</P>
<P>
   Iona, one of UCLA's early-season victims, won the Metro Atlantic
Athletic Conference title and earned an NCAA bid.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins' victory over Stanford was their first over a No. 1
team in 13 years (North Carolina) and their seventh overall. Notre
Dame leads all schools with nine victories over top-ranked teams,
according to the Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday's game against Washington State will not be televised.
Call 310-UCLA-WIN for tickets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
